    "Within professional personas, model heterogeneity ranges from 2.8% to 73.6%.",
    "This 26-fold variation demonstrates that some models maintain robust disclosure while others fail almost entirely.",
    "Fig. 4.4Fig.",
    "Models under 10B parameters.",
    "Even at the smallest scale, variation exists (2.8% to 35.4%), demonstrating that parameter count alone does not determine disclosure rates."
